\lim_{x\to 1} \frac{4x^2 - 4}{x-1}?
\require{cancel}
\frac{4x^2-4}{x-1}=\frac{4(x^2-1)}{x-1}=\frac{4\cancel{(x-1})(x+1)}{\cancel{x-1}}=\;\;4(x+1) \;\;\;\text{when}\;x \neq 1
\lim_{x \to 1} 4(x + 1)
\frac{4x^2-4}{x-1}=\frac{4(x^2-1)}{x-1}=\frac{4(x-1)(x+1)}{x-1}=4(x+1)\text{  if }x-1\ne0
